            "role": "assistant",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Machine learning is a part of AI where computers **learn patterns from data to make predictions or decisions**, instead of being programmed with fixed rules.\n\nTypical examples:\n- **Spam filtering:** learning which emails look like spam from labeled examples  \n- **Image recognition:** learning to identify objects from many images  \n- **Recommendations:** learning what you might like based on past behavior\n\nCommon types of machine learning:\n- **Supervised learning:** learns from labeled data (e.g., “spam” vs “not spam”)  \n- **Unsupervised learning:** finds structure in unlabeled data (e.g., clustering customers)  \n- **Reinforcement learning:** learns by trial and error using rewards (e.g., game-playing agents)",
